# We want to use the latest microcode in our CPUs.
# In general the microcode-kernel-module itself looks for updates once loaded.
# Since we have that module compiled in, we currently need microcode-ctl
# to be able to reload/update microcodes without rebooting.
# With kernel 3.6 we will be able to do
#     echo 1 > /sys/devices/system/cpu/microcode/reload
# at which point we won't be needing microcode-ctl anymore.
*sys-apps/microcode-data
*sys-apps/microcode-ctl

*sys-process/iotop
